note.summary:
Terraform files usually end in .tf and are often split as main.tf, providers.tf, variables.tf, outputs.tf, and versions.tf. The core idea is declaring what should exist.

Tiny example:
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "example" {
  bucket = "example-learning-bucket"
}

This declares intent; nothing is created until the workflow runs.

Tiny example:
output "bucket_name" {
  value = aws_s3_bucket.example.bucket
}

Outputs help scripts, tools, and teammates consume created values safely.
